  <description type="morphology">Annuals or biennials; rhizomes none. Stems sparsely and loosely strigose (hairs ascending to spreading, 0.5–1 mm). Leaves: basal broadly oblanceolate or oblanceolate, 5–15(–20) mm wide, margins usually dentate, faces sparsely strigose or strigoso-hirsute. Involucres (2.5–)3–4 mm. Phyllaries strigose (hairs flattened, 0.5–1.2 mm).</description>
